Question: What is included in Edens dorm?
chat_answer: Edens Quad, renovated in 2016, accommodates approximately 500 students across its seven buildings. Each room is furnished with a full-size bed, bookcase, three-drawer chest, closet with a mirror, and a desk with a task chair. Beyond individual rooms, Edens offers extensive common amenities including multiple kitchens, shared common spaces, and dedicated study areas. Residents also have access to e-print services, laundry facilities, a fitness room, and a yoga/dance space. Elevators are available across the quad, and there are multiple outdoor spaces for house events. Additionally, Edens Quad is conveniently located near Pitchfork's restaurant and Bella Union coffee shop in McClendon Tower. The quad is supported by a Residence Coordinator, an Academic Guide, two Graduate Residents, and 15 Resident Assistants.
my_answer:
Built in the late 1960s and renovated in 2016, Edens Quad is home to approximately 500 students. Edens offers multiple kitchens and common spaces, e-print, laundry, a fitness room, and yoga space. Edens Quad has a Residence Coordinator, an Academic Guide, two Graduate Residents and 15 Resident Assistants. 

Building Features
Fitness room and yoga/dance space
Laundry
Elevators located across the quad
Rooms vary in size and shape
Multiple outdoor spaces for house events and gatherings.
Close access to Pitchfork's restaurant and Bella Union coffee shop, located in McClendon Tower.

Full-size bed
Bookcase
Three-drawer chest
Closet with mirror
Desk and task chair
Commons, Kitchenettes & Restrooms
Common areas, kitchens, and study areas are available in each of the seven buildings that make up Edens Quad. Several buildings in Edens have "lower" sections (bottom two floors) and "upper" sections (top two floors), and each section has dedicated common areas for residents who live nearby.

Question: How do I do laundry at duke?
chat_answer: Laundry machines are available in designated laundry rooms located throughout all Duke residence halls. For many students, these machines are DukeCard and coin-operated, allowing for payment using either method. However, some residence halls, particularly those for first-year students, offer free laundry services. This service is managed by Duke Vending. If you encounter a broken machine or require reimbursement due to lost money, you should contact Duke Vending directly at 919-684-8363. Additionally, your HRL Campus Office can assist you in reaching out to Duke Vending for machine repairs. For any other issues related to the laundry facilities, you can call the East Campus Office at 919-684-5320 or contact your HRL Campus Office.
my_answer: DukeCard and coin-operated laundry machines are located in laundry rooms throughout the residence halls. This service is provided through Duke Vending. To report broken machines or to request reimbursement when money is lost in the machines, call Duke Vending at 684-8363. Your HRL Campus Office will be happy to help you contact Duke Vending to get machines repaired. To report any other problems with the laundry facilities please call your HRL Campus Office.

Question: i need help with mailing packages

Question: my ac is not working properly what should i do
chat_answer: If your AC is not working properly, you should contact your HRL Campus Office to report the problem, providing as much detail as possible. During business hours (Monday-Friday, 9:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.), you can submit a Residential Work Order Request online. For non-emergency issues, a work order is sufficient. If it's an emergency issue during business hours, you should call the respective office in addition to filling out the Work Order Request. Specific contact numbers are available: East Campus at 919-684-5320 and West Campus at 919-684-5486. For after-hours support, you should contact your Resident Assistant (RA) or Graduate Resident (GR) on call, whose pager numbers are usually posted on the quad's exterior doors.
my_answer: If it's not too bad, submit a work order but If you feel that your room is too cold or too hot  call your HRL Campus Office to report the problem. Provide as much information as possible. Remember you can contact the HRL office between 9am- 5pm on weekdays.At othertimes contact the RA-on call or the Grad-on call

Question: what do you need to be eligible to apply for RA position
chat_answer: To be eligible for an RA position, a candidate must have a 2.5 cumulative GPA and be in good standing with the University. Applicants must also be able to begin the RA/CA role in Spring 2026 or August 2026.
my_answer:
RAs and CAs must be full-time enrolled, degree-seeking students in good academic standing at Duke University and must maintain a cumulative 2.5 GPA while in their position. Undergraduate, graduate, and professional degree students are eligible for the RA and CA positions. 
RAs and CAs may not enroll in more than five (5) units, per semester without approval from their supervisor. 
RAs and CAs must also remain in good conduct and disciplinary standing with the university at all times. This includes adhering to all University and Housing & Residence Life policies as outlined in the Duke Community Standard Guide and Housing License. 
Must be willing to adhere to all positional conditions and expectations outlined in the position description.
